  <title translate="true">loop system</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">A</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">set of vectors in a survey form a</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;" translate="true"> loop system</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true"> if given any two vectors in the set there exists at least one loop in the set containing them both. &#160;In a least-squares adjustment, </text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">one</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true"> vector&apos;s measurement contributes to the final estimates of </text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">all</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true"> vectors in the loop system that contains it. See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Terminology" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">Network Terminology</link><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">.</text></para>
  </body>
